# Generable(description:)

**Macro**

Conforms a type to [doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/Generable] protocol.

## Declaration

```swift
@attached(extension, conformances: Generable, names: named(init(_:)), named(generatedContent)) @attached(member, names: arbitrary) macro Generable(description: String? = nil)
```

## Overview

You can apply this macro to structures and enumerations.

```swift
@Generable
struct NovelIdea {
  @Guide(description: "A short title")
  let title: String

  @Guide(description: "A short subtitle for the novel")
  let subtitle: String

  @Guide(description: "The genre of the novel")
  let genre: Genre
}

@Generable
enum Genre {
  case fiction
  case nonFiction
}
```
